PENSACOLA STATION ( AMTRAK )
Pensacola station is a former train station in Pensacola , Florida .
It was served by Amtrak , the national railroad passenger system .
The station served as a replacement for the former Louisville and Nashville Passenger Station and Express Building .
Service has been suspended since Hurricane Katrina struck Pensacola in 2005 .
However , service is proposed to return in the near future , bringing back the Sunset Limited to this station .
